{'question': 'I’m having trouble with a Model 18 ADA dishwasher. It’s showing an error code E4 and isn’t draining.', 'response': ' The error code E4 on your Model 18 ADA dishwasher indicates an overflow issue. Here are some steps you can take to troubleshoot the problem:\n\n   1. Check the Thermistor: Make sure that the thermistor is working correctly as it controls the heating of the water in the dishwasher.\n\n   2. Check the Control: Ensure that the control is functioning properly. The control regulates various functions, including the drain cycle.\n\n   3. "Light" Indicator Flashes: If water flows into the base and activates the overflow switch, the dishwasher will display E4.1. In this case, check the use of the detergent to ensure it is not causing the overflow.\n\n     Since the dishwasher isn\'t draining, you may also want to inspect the drain pump and impeller for any blockages or malfunctions. Additionally, verify that the door latch is engaging properly to prevent water from leaking out during the wash cycle.', 'expected_keywords': [], 'expected_sources': [], 'latency_s': 8.956350326538086}
