{'question': 'I’m having trouble with a Model 18 ADA dishwasher. It’s showing an error code E4 and isn’t draining.', 'response': ' Based on the error code E4 you\'re experiencing, it seems like your dishwasher is overflowing. Here are some steps to troubleshoot the issue:\n\n   1. Check the Thermistor: The thermistor measures the water temperature inside the dishwasher. If it\'s faulty, it may not be able to detect when the wash cycle has ended, causing the dishwasher to continue filling with water and overflowing.\n\n   2. Check the Control: The control board of your dishwasher manages various functions, including the draining process. If there\'s an issue with the control board, it may not be properly activating the drain pump.\n\n   The "Light" indicator flashing overflow suggests that water is flowing into the base and activating the overflow switch. Here are some additional steps to help you diagnose the problem:\n\n   3. Check the use of Detergent: Ensure you\'re using the right amount of detergent according to the manufacturer\'s instructions. Excessive detergent can cause the dishwasher to overflow.\n\n   If the problem persists after following these steps, it might be best to contact a professional appliance repair service or consult the user manual for further assistance.', 'expected_keywords': [], 'expected_sources': [], 'latency_s': 10.093900203704834}
