{'question': 'I’m having trouble with a Model 18 ADA dishwasher. It’s showing an error code E4 and isn’t draining.', 'response': ' The error code E4 on the Model 18 ADA dishwasher typically indicates an overflow issue. Here are the steps to troubleshoot:\n\n   1. Check the Thermistor: Ensure that the thermistor, which measures the temperature of the water in the dishwasher, is functioning correctly. If it\'s faulty, replace it.\n\n   2. Check the Control: Examine the control module to see if there are any issues with it. If necessary, you may need to replace the control.\n\n   3. "Light" Indicator Flashes Overflow: If water flows into the base and activates the overflow switch, the dishwasher will display E4. Check for any leaks or clogs in the drain hose that might cause water to overflow.\n\n   4. Check the Use of the Detergent: Verify if the recommended amount of detergent is being used. Excessive detergent can cause issues with draining and may trigger error code E4.', 'expected_keywords': [], 'expected_sources': [], 'latency_s': 8.995396137237549}
